<seg id=1> Primary and Middle Schools in the Disaster Areas of Zhejiang Province Open for Class Normally </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Hangzhou, September 2, Telegram (Reporters Shen Haixiong and Shen Xiquan).  The No. 17 typhoon has caused disastrous losses to the education system in the disaster areas of Zhejiang Province, with school dormitories and facilities in as many as 1500 schools damaged. </seg>
<seg id=3> With the active fighting against the disaster and the all-out self-help efforts, most of the primary and middle schools have opened for class normally at the moment. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Recently, the education department of Zhejiang Province dispatched working teams to disaster areas such as Wenzhou and Taizhou to provide guidance to the restoration of the education system. </seg>
<seg id=5> The Wenzhou Education Commission organized seven groups of over 20 government functionaries to go to Leqing, Ouhai, Tongtou, and Pingyang and help on school campus restoration and school-opening preparation. In addition, the commission drew 200,000RMB from the education funds for special disaster relief of the education system. </seg>
<seg id=6> The education administration agencies in the cities and counties of the disaster areas granted tuition exemption or sponsored part tuition to students who are unable to pay the tuition due to the family hardship caused by the disaster, ensuring that the students can go to school on schedule.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> School leaders, teachers, and staff in the disaster areas voluntarily go to work before time to seriously clean up and sterilize school campuses, and repair the damaged school dormitories.  </seg>
<seg id=8> The Wenzhou Education Commission and Communist League Wenhou Committee, joined with teachers and students of schools from disaster areas, sponsored a donation activity of "Love Hearts for Schools Hit by the Disaster". So far, donation of over one million RMB has been received from all walks of life in Wenzhou city. </seg>
</p>
